A protein that consist of a single copy of the Aminotransferase class I and II (Pfam:PF00155) domain. Alpha-oxoamine synthase corresponds to the alpha-division of pyridoxal-5'-phosphate (PLP)-dependent enzymes. Alpha-oxoamine synthase are involved in catalysis of the decarboxylative condensation of a carboxylic acid coenzyme A (CoA) thioester and an amino acid, with the amino acid being covalently bound to the PLP via a Schiff base at the beginning of the catalytic cycle.

A PLP-dependent alpha-oxoamine synthase whose functional form is the first enzyme in the pathway for synthesis of all tetrapyrroles in non-photosynthetic eukaryotes and alpha-proteobacteria. ALAS catalyzes the decarboxylative condensation of glycine and succinyl-CoA, yielding 5-aminolevulinic acid, free coenzyme-A and CO2.
A PLP-dependent alpha-oxoamine synthase that is involved in sphingolipid biosynthesis in Eukaryota, particularly in the condensation of L-serine and palmitoyl-CoA.
A PLP-dependent alpha-oxoamine synthase that is a translation product of the Sphingomonas paucimobilis spt1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
